Trigger: is function or set of instructions/command which
execute automatically when DML(data manipulation language)
command will run/execute/fire on an object
===============
Automatically: trigger cannot be call/execute explicitly 
		-this will exectue automatically
DML:
	->new row / insert row
	->update / edit row
	->delete / remove row 


There are following types of trigger:
i. before 		
		insert/new row
		update / edit
		delete / remove
ii. after 
		insert
		update
		delete 


====================================
Example1:
Object :
	oid		: 
	customer name	:
	product name	:
	qty		:
	price		:

	*	Action from trigger
	Total Price ?
	Tax	    ? 
	
	* Assign the particular order to sales person 
	SalesPerson?
		SP1
		SP2
		SP3	
	

Step1:
	create an object : Sales_Order
Step2:
	add the required/above menstion columns
Step3:
	add object to tab 
	
Step4: 
	create before insert trigger 


trigger trg_before_up on Sales_Order__c (before insert) {

}


	if (country  == 'india')
	{
		o.sale.. = 'kshitiz johar'
	}
	else if (country  =='us')
	{
		gaurav kapoor
	}
	else 
	{
		nitin sinha
	}
	
